        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-10T23:45:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In the luci-go codebase, only two functions accept a context by reference, so this was pretty surprising for me to see when I first saw it, and took me a while to figure out what it did.\n\ngo/src/go.chromium.org/luci$ git grep \"*context.Context\"\nlogdog/appengine/coordinator/context.go:func WithProjectNamespace(c *context.Context, project types.ProjectName, at NamespaceAccessType) error {\nlogdog/server/service/service.go:func (s *Service) initConfig(c *context.Context) error {\n\nI think for consistency, it\u0027s be better to change the other two functions to return a copy of the context instead.  (I\u0027d do this in a separate CL)",
      "parentUuid": "cda4236c_3603d331",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 84,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 84,
        "endChar": 147
      },
      "revId": "2c65001216bec4ec10a938fe75e39de80d0e2068",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
