      "writtenOn": "2018-05-14T21:02:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I see, I didn\u0027t know this was discussed before. I see the benefits of the Something(\u0026c) semantics (since i did screw it up the first time without realizing it), but I think I disagree on the triviality of the price.  I think consistency is rather important to avoid throwing people off, so we should either:\n\nWithin a single code base, pick one:\n* c \u003d With(c)\n* With(\u0026c)  // And make the caller copy the context if needed.\n\nBut not use both.\n\nI\u0027ll try to remember these points though the next time this is discussed.",
      "parentUuid": "d983216b_ec2ef781",
