    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "688cbd49_40a48bad",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 141,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-10T23:45:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Cloning params seems fine, since:\n* path is just a string, so it\u0027s basically pass by reference\n* storage.Storage is an interface, but I think its usually a pointer\n* LogStreamState is already a pointer.\n\nIt basically makes it the same as if they were passed as real params.  The plus side of cloning it is that since we don\u0027t need to modify anything to send upstream, the caller can be rest assured that data flows in one direction.\n\nWell i guess except for the LogStreamState, since its a pointer :/",
      "parentUuid": "c60e73f6_64eb6e46",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 141,
        "startChar": 56,
        "endLine": 141,
        "endChar": 67
      },
      "revId": "2c65001216bec4ec10a938fe75e39de80d0e2068",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1734fe2f_e8bde3f3",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 141,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-10T23:45:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "They\u0027re fine sometimes, other times they become kind of a headache if someone has to dig through a few layer of indirection to figure out what a few lines of code means, or figuring out which variables are inputs and which ones are outputs.  I don\u0027t have a great answer that fits everywhere, just trying to find a good balance.",
      "parentUuid": "f69d42df_035faab7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 141,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 141,
        "endChar": 10
      },
      "revId": "2c65001216bec4ec10a938fe75e39de80d0e2068",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d8324581_20a0d0ef",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 141,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-11T13:37:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah - my rule of thumb is that unless there\u0027s an explicit purpose to passing by value, just pass by reference. Passing by value can be counterintuitive. I don\u0027t think anything is gained here by doing it, so I\u0027d recommend going by reference *shrug*\n\nThis is something Go\u0027s not super great at being clear on.",
      "parentUuid": "688cbd49_40a48bad",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 141,
        "startChar": 56,
        "endLine": 141,
        "endChar": 67
      },
      "revId": "2c65001216bec4ec10a938fe75e39de80d0e2068",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fe8b6d0b_f6a2b87f",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 141,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-14T21:02:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "FAQ prefers value over pointers receivers for small structs:\nhttps://golang.org/doc/faq#pass_by_value\n\"For types such as basic types, slices, and small structs, a value receiver is very cheap so unless the semantics of the method requires a pointer, a value receiver is efficient and clear.\"\n\nAnd it could be cheaper since it\u0027s less work for Go\u0027s escape analysis:\nhttp://goinbigdata.com/golang-pass-by-pointer-vs-pass-by-value/\n\"Passing by value often is cheaper\"\n\nI think as a rule of thumb I like passing by value unless there\u0027s a need for a pointer because it makes some things simpler, like:\n* No need to worry about nil dereferences\n* No need to worry about leakage.",
      "parentUuid": "d8324581_20a0d0ef",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 141,
        "startChar": 56,
        "endLine": 141,
        "endChar": 67
      },
